*Problem Definition*

Currently in JIRA is a user uploaded an attachment, JIRA will be storing the file in {{<JIRAHOME>/data/attachment}} and rename the attached file to a numbered file such as "10001".

Say for example an user uploaded test.pdf to an issue with issue id SKP-1, the pdf file will be stored in followed directory:

{code:java}
/home/vicknesh/JIRA/Home/jira7home/data/attachments/SKP/10000/SKP-1/10001
{code}

*Suggested Solution*

Allow JIRA to store the attached file with the original name and format.

*Workaround*

Currently there's no workaround for this.

