h2.Summary

There are 2 types of permission in JIRA, Global and project level permissions. This is not properly highlighted in the documentation. This is the documentation on the permission query.

* https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/latest/#api/2/user-findUsersWithAllPermissions

The above link didn't really specify that there global and project level permissions. Not knowing this, users sometimes try to search for global permissions on project level. 

*Doesn't Work* - {{https://testinstance.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user/permission/search?permissions=SYSTEM_ADMIN&projectKey=<PROJECT_KEY>}}

*Works* - {{https://testinstance.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user/permission/search?permissions=SYSTEM_ADMIN}}

The reason the first one doesn't work is because sysadmin is a global permission; finding a global permission on project level will fail. This is expected but wasn't highlighted in the documentation. Perhaps global and project permissions should be highlighted at {{https://developer.atlassian.com/static/javadoc/jira/6.0/reference/com/atlassian/jira/security/Permissions.Permission.html?_ga=1.110401797.183676958.1465802124}} ?

